fields.prompt: How are you feeling?
What are your goals? Think big and think small. Be realistic and unrealistic too.
Describe your day, today. Did you enjoy it? What did you do? Is there anything you would have preferred to do?
What's on your bucket list? Write down 100 things you plan to do with your life and start ticking them off.
What are you grateful for? List all the things that you are grateful for. Because not everything sucks, and you know it.
What does home mean to you? Think about all the homes you've had. What made them feel like home? Where do you call home? Where do you feel most at home?
What's on your mind? List all the things on your mind. Good or bad, jobs or chores. Absolutely everything you can think of.
When do you remember having the most fun? Describe where you were and who you were with. Why does it stick in your memory and how could you relive it?
Do you love what you do? Is there anything you could change about your career so far? Maybe you're working too hard or too much. How could you balance this out?
What's your relationship with money? Does it have a positive or negative effect on your life? Are you happy with the relationship you have built?
Who are your role models? Think about the role models you've had in your life and how they've influenced you. What made them a role model? Who could be your new role model and why?
List your greatest strengths and weaknesses. What three weaknesses could you turn into new strengths? How could you achieve this?
Reflect on your relationships. How have they had an impact on you? What have you learned from each one?
What's your biggest fear? Describe how this fear makes you feel. How do you manage this fear? Does it prevent you from doing anything? How could you confront this fear?
What makes you angry? Describe the last time you got angry. How did you feel before, during and after? How do you deal with your anger?
How does crying make you feel? Think about the last time you shed a tear. What was it over? What's your relationship with crying? When do you feel it's acceptable to cry?
Who would you like to forgive? What would you say to them if you had a chance? How does holding a grudge against someone make you feel?
Write a letter to someone, past or present. What do you want to tell them? Is there something you wish you could say but are too afraid?
What's on your f*ck it list? Write down all the things in your life that you think are important, but aren't. What things do you spend time on because you think you 'should'?
Who and what do you find it hard to say no to? Why is this? How does saying no make you feel? What would happen if you said no?
What brings you joy? What activity do you love doing but rarely get the opportunity to do? When are you truly happy and time disappears?
What's the one thing you're always putting off? What's stopping you from doing it? What needs to be done to achieve it? How will you do it?
How would you spend your time if you had complete freedom? What have you always dreamed of doing? Remember, you write your own story.
What's missing from your life? It could be a sense of purpose, passion, fun or even adventure. What could you  do to find more of it in your life. What's holding you back?
What is your role? How does it feel to be you?  What is expected of you? What kind of person would you like to be?
Write down what you would say to yourself in the face of a tough situation. Remind yourself of your strengths and qualities.
What's your game plan? Where do you want your life to be in two years? Think of what kind of person you want to be, the life you want to live and the things you want to achieve.
Who's got your back? Think about your friends, family and co-workers. Who supports you? Can you talk to them honestly and openly? How could you have your own back?
